seafile-server (13.0.25-1~alpha2) unstable; urgency=medium

  * debian: patch the missing fsck include instead of demoting compiler errors
  * debian: use the distribution libsearpc, track pinned libevhtp via uscan
  * debian: directory-level config confidentiality, migrations without CLI database tools or backups
  * debian: units for trixie+ only, read-only config mounts, add seaf-fuse and seaf-notification services
  * debian: merge seahub into seafile-server, split seafile-fuse and arch-independent seafile-server-data
  * docs+ci: follow the new packaging layout

 -- dionysius <dragon.dionysius@gmail.com>  Sun, 19 Jul 2026 14:17:37 +0200

seafile-server (13.0.25-1~alpha1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Initial packaging of Seafile Community Edition server (v13), built from
    source without docker
  * single source package with seafile-server as the main upstream; libsearpc,
    libevhtp, seahub, seafobj, seafdav and seafevents are pulled in by tag as
    upstream components and compiled together
  * produces seafile-server (daemons), seahub (Django web frontend, python via
    uv), libsearpc (RPC library) and the seafile metapackage
  * SQLite backend by default, MySQL/MariaDB backend supported
  * NOT CRITICALLY AUTHORED, EVERYTHING CAN CHANGE, STEPS STILL REQUIRE
    GOOD THOUGHT FOR PLANNED COMPATIBILITY/MAINTENANCE FLOWS

 -- dionysius <dragon.dionysius@gmail.com>  Tue, 14 Jul 2026 01:04:18 +0200
